Migraines:
• Unlike normal headaches, a migraine makes a person immobile
• When a person gets a migraine attack, the only thing he'll want to do is  lie down in a quiet place

Symptoms to look for:
• Localized pain on one side of the head
• Pulsating sensation behind the eye
• The pain may shift to other side of the head on another occasion
• Vomiting
• Nausea
• Diarrhoea
• Cold hands and feet
• Sensitivity to light

Causes:
• Intake of alcohol
• Drugs
• Smoking
• Allergic reactions
• Drop in blood sugar level
• Nutritional deficiencies
• Lack of sleep
• Excessive work
• Menopause

